**The LiLa™ Family**

AI Magic for Moms --- Intelligent Assistant System

*Current Versions & Capabilities Guide*

LiLa™ (short for "Little Lady") is the intelligent assistant system at
the heart of AIMfM. Rather than one monolithic AI, LiLa is split into
specialized versions, each with a distinct personality, purpose, and
avatar. This approach lets families interact with the right kind of help
at the right time --- from troubleshooting a login issue to crafting a
deeply personalized AI prompt.

All LiLa versions share the same warm, encouraging brand voice and
visual style, but each serves a unique role in the ecosystem.

1\. LiLa™ Help --- "Happy to Help"

  --------------------- -------------------------------------------------
  **Subtitle**          Happy to Help

  **Avatar Image**      Lila-HtH.png

  **Primary Role**      Customer support & troubleshooting

  **Current Status**    Frontend shell built; AI responses not yet
                        connected
  --------------------- -------------------------------------------------

What She Does

LiLa Help is the first line of support for anyone using the AIMfM
platform. She handles the practical, operational side of things --- the
stuff that would normally go to a help desk or FAQ page, but delivered
with warmth and personality instead of dry documentation.

-   Login and account issues (password resets, access problems)

-   Billing and subscription questions (tier changes, payment issues)

-   Technical troubleshooting (features not loading, browser
    compatibility)

-   General platform FAQ and quick answers

How She Works

Currently, LiLa Help uses pattern-matching on user input to provide
pre-written responses for common issues. The component is built as a
modal chat interface accessible from the LiLa Panel in the global
header. In future phases, she will connect to OpenRouter for more
dynamic, context-aware support responses.

2\. LiLa™ Assist --- "Your Guide"

  --------------------- -------------------------------------------------
  **Subtitle**          Your Guide

  **Avatar Image**      lila-asst.png

  **Primary Role**      Feature guidance, onboarding, and tool
                        recommendations

  **Current Status**    Frontend shell built; AI responses not yet
                        connected
  --------------------- -------------------------------------------------

What She Does

LiLa Assist is the in-app guide who helps users discover and learn the
AIMfM ecosystem. Think of her as a knowledgeable friend who knows every
feature and can walk you through anything --- from setting up your
family profile for the first time to discovering a hidden shortcut you
never knew existed.

-   Getting started walkthroughs (family profile setup, preferences,
    navigation)

-   Feature guidance and tips for using any AIMfM tool effectively

-   Tool recommendations based on what a user is trying to accomplish

-   Tutorial suggestions from the Library Vault

-   Optimization tips for getting more value from the subscription

How She Works

Like LiLa Help, Assist currently uses keyword-based response generation
in a modal chat interface. She detects topics like tasks, archives,
library, and themes to provide contextual guidance. Future phases will
connect her to OpenRouter and the Library Vault content system so she
can recommend specific tutorials and walk users through complex
workflows interactively.

3\. LiLa™ Optimizer --- "Smart AI"

  --------------------- -------------------------------------------------
  **Subtitle**          Smart AI

  **Avatar Image**      lila-opt.png

  **Primary Role**      Prompt optimization with family context awareness

  **Current Status**    Frontend shell built; core AI integration planned
                        for Phase 3
  --------------------- -------------------------------------------------

What She Does

LiLa Optimizer is the flagship intelligence layer of AIMfM --- the
version that makes everything else valuable. She takes a simple request
from Mom and transforms it into a rich, context-aware prompt that any AI
platform can understand deeply. This is where the Archives, Best
Intentions, and family context all come together.

-   Fix broken prompts --- diagnose why prompts aren't working and
    rewrite them

-   Create new prompts from scratch for any task, with role-playing and
    structure

-   Optimize existing prompts by adding family context, specificity, and
    platform formatting

-   Learn from conversations --- detect new family information and
    suggest saving to Archives

-   Platform-specific formatting (ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Midjourney,
    etc.)

How She Works (Planned Architecture)

The Optimizer follows an 80/20 cost strategy: 80% of operations are
handled through fast JavaScript processing (pattern matching, template
insertion, context assembly) and only 20% hit the AI API via OpenRouter
for complex reasoning. This keeps costs under \$1.50 per family per
month.

**Optimization Flow:** Mom types a simple request → LiLa detects
mentioned family members → Retrieves relevant context from Archives →
Pulls active Best Intentions → Crafts an optimized, platform-specific
prompt → Mom copies/pastes to her preferred AI platform.

**Context Learning:** When Mom mentions new information in conversation
(e.g., "Jake hates broccoli now"), the Optimizer detects it, asks Mom's
permission, and suggests saving it to the appropriate Archives folder
for future use.

**Library Integration:** Library tools include an "Optimize with LiLa"
button that passes tool details and family context to the Optimizer,
generating a personalized version of any prompt template.

4\. LiLa™ API --- "The Engine"

  --------------------- -------------------------------------------------
  **Subtitle**          Backend Intelligence

  **Avatar Image**      N/A (no user-facing avatar)

  **Primary Role**      Backend AI processing, formatting, and edge-case
                        handling

  **Current Status**    Planned; will initially use OpenRouter,
                        eventually a self-hosted fine-tuned model
  --------------------- -------------------------------------------------

What It Does

LiLa API is the behind-the-scenes engine that powers the other LiLa
versions. It's not a character users interact with directly --- it's the
infrastructure that handles the actual AI calls, content formatting, and
processing that the other versions need to do their jobs.

-   Connected to OpenRouter for multi-model AI access

-   Handles primarily JavaScript-based content formatting and
    beautification

-   Processes small AI jobs and edge-case requests

-   Eventually will be replaced by a fine-tuned, self-hosted model

How It Works

LiLa API serves as the shared backend for all user-facing LiLa versions.
When the Optimizer needs to make a complex AI call, it routes through
LiLa API. When Assist needs to generate a dynamic tutorial
recommendation, it queries LiLa API. The long-term vision is to
fine-tune a model specifically on AIMfM's family context patterns and
optimization strategies, then self-host it for maximum cost control and
customization.

Quick Comparison

  ------------------ ------------- --------------- -------------- -------------
                     **LiLa Help** **LiLa Assist** **LiLa         **LiLa API**
                                                   Optimizer**    

  **Subtitle**       Happy to Help Your Guide      Smart AI       The Engine

  **User-Facing?**   Yes           Yes             Yes            No

  **Has Avatar?**    Yes           Yes             Yes            No

  **Primary Focus**  Support       Guidance        Intelligence   Processing

  **Uses AI API?**   Future        Future          Yes (planned)  Yes

  **Dev Status**     Shell built   Shell built     Shell built    Planned
  ------------------ ------------- --------------- -------------- -------------

How They Work Together

All four LiLa versions are accessible through the LiLa Panel component
in the global header. The three user-facing versions (Help, Assist,
Optimizer) each appear as a character card that users can click to open
a modal chat interface. Behind the scenes, they all route through LiLa
API for any AI-powered processing.

The versions are designed to be complementary, not overlapping. A user
who can't figure out how to use a feature talks to **LiLa Help**. A user
who wants to learn what they can do with a feature talks to **LiLa
Assist**. A user who wants to use AI more effectively with their family
context talks to **LiLa Optimizer**. And **LiLa API** quietly powers
them all.

*AI Magic for Moms --- Real magic for real moms*

